<HEADLINE>Dying baby sent home</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>4</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974635116</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
A BABY boy died of meningitis hours after being sent home from a hospital
casualty unit late at night, it was disclosed yesterday.
Five-week-old Ryan Smith from Londonderry's Creggan district was later
confirmed to have had meningococcal meningitis.
His mother, Wendy, first became worried about Ryan on the evening of the
Thursday before Christmas and called out her GP, who examined him and said he
might have meningitis.
With her boyfriend Paul Boreland, she took the baby immediately to Altnagelvin
hospital, where a doctor told her to go home and return next day if the baby's
condition did not improve.
The baby died in bed beside his mother about 7am the next day.
A coroner's inquiry is to be held but the hospital said it does not plan an
internal inquiry.
</TEXT>
