<TEXT>
POLICE divers are to search a lake as fears grow that a child may have drowned
in the freezing water.
Officers found a set of footprints leading from the bank at Temple Lake, in
Nuthall, Nottinghamshire, across the frozen water to a hole in the ice, 15 feet
out. They said there was no trace of footprints returning to the bank.
A search by officers from the Nottinghamshire Fire and Rescue Service failed to
find any trace of a child. Nottinghamshire Police say no-one in the area has
been reported missing but the incident is being treated as suspicious.
Divers from the force's underwater investigation unit will mount a full search
early today.
</TEXT>
