<HEADLINE>Athletics</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>24</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974635149</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
BRITAIN'S Jonathan Edwards yesterday collected his fifth major award of the
year when he was voted ``champion of the champions, 1995'' by the influential
French sports daily, l'Equipe. Edwards, first man to break 18 metres when he
won the world triple jum
p title in Gothenburg, finished ahead of Michael Johnson, winner of the 200 and
400m, and Miguel Indurain, who won a record fifth consecutive Tour de France.
