<TEXT>
TWO Scots golfers who reached the pinnacle of their careers in 1995 and a woman
rugby stalwart in Stranraer have been honoured
Bernard Gallacher and George Macgregor have followed similar paths in the
parallel professional and amateur golfing worlds, culminating this year in the
Ryder and Walker Cup successes against the United States, (writes Douglas Lowe).
Gallacher, 46, from Bathgate, was captain of Europe for the third and final
time, while Macgregor, 51, of the Glencorse club in Penicuik, following four
years as Walker Cup captain, was this year chairman of selectors for the Great
Britain and Ireland sid
e which was coached, co-incidentally, by Gallacher.
The pair were Lothians team-mates in the late sixties.
It is appropriate that both should receive their OBEs together.
Mrs Jessie Ferguson, MBE, now 77, has been associated with Stranraer Rugby Club
since it was founded half-a-century ago.
Mrs Ferguson got involved with the club through her late husband, William, a
lawyer, and their son, William, who were both players.
</TEXT>
