<TEXT>
RUSSIAN diver Yelena Miroshina, a silver medallist at the 1992 Olympic Games in
Barcelona, has been found dead outside of her Moscow apartment.
She either jumped or was pushed from a window on the fifth floor, said a duty
officer for Moscow police.
Miroshina took highboard silver medals at the 1992 Olympics and the 1991 world
championships. She was European highboard champion in 1987 and 1991.
</TEXT>
