<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>4</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974635166</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
A GENERAL safety certificate for Tynecastle Park, the home of Heart of
Midlothian Football Club, has been extended to include continued use of its
seating until the end of this season.
Lothian Regional Council said yesterday it had wanted Hearts legally to agree
to build a new stand by Sunday, December 31, but was now satisfied the club had
sufficiently progressed the planning for the stand.
The council also agreed to sell a former technical block at Norton Park,
Edinburgh, to Hibernian Football Club for conversion to office space.
