<HEADLINE>Double boost for cup tourney</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>24</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974635175</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
FRANCE and the United States have given the Hopman Cup a boost, stepping in to
replace Sweden and Ukraine who have withdrawn from the mixed team tournament in
Perth.
Sweden pulled out earlier this week after former world No.1 Mats Wilander
suffered a back injury.
The US and France have filled the last two places in group A behind Croatians
Goran Ivanisevic and Iva Majoli, and South Africans Wayne Ferreira and Amanda
Coetzer.
American pair Richey Reneberg and Chanda Rubin open their campaign on Monday
against South Africa, while Croatia take on the French pair, Arnaud Boetsch and
Catherine Tanvier.
Group B has three of the biggest servers in men's tennis - Richard Krajicek of
the Netherlands, Switzerland's Marc Rosset and Mark Philippoussis of Australia.
Krajicek and Brenda Schultz-McCarthy are seeded at the top of the group, ahead
of Rosset and teenage prodigy Martina Hingis.
Philippoussis and Nicole Bradtke are next, ahead of defending champions
Germany, weakened by the unavailability of world No.4 Boris Becker.
</TEXT>
