<RECORDNO>974635176</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
VATICAN CITY: The Vatican said more than 300,000 people contacted its new
Internet connection over Christmas, with hundreds sending get-well messages to
the Pope. He had to cut short his Christmas message after suffering flu and
doctors have told him to r
est until Sunday. One message, from a computer user identified only as Sarah,
advised him to drink lots of liquids and chicken broth.
