<HEADLINE>Testing time ahead</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>24</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974635181</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
SCOTLAND will play two tests against the host country - at Carisbrook and Eden
Park - on their eight match tour of New Zealand next summer. The Scots open
against third division provincial side, Wanganui before facing Northland at
Whangerei.
The hardest match for the tourists outside the two Tests is expected to be
against Waikato.
Compared to Scotland's 1990 tour when they were undefeated in the six non-test
games, the 1996 itinerary looks marginally less arduous.
May 28 v Wanganui (Wanganui); May 31 v Northland (Whangerei); June 5 v Waikato
(Hamilton); June 8 v Southland (Invercargill); June 11 v South Island
Divisional XV (Blenheim); June 15 v New Zealand (Dundedin); June 18 v Bay of
Plenty (Rotorua); June 22 v N
ew Zealand (Auckland).
</TEXT>
