<HEADLINE>No Headline Present</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>5</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974635182</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
SANTA Claus has posted #850 to Royal Hospital for Sick Children, Yorkhill,
Glasgow. The red envelope, posted in the city on December 28, contained the
money in used notes and a piece of simple lined notepaper, on which was
written: ``For the sick children
, from Santa Claus''.
The gift was discovered by clerkess Lynda Watt, who opened the mail yesterday.
The money will be given to the children's fund and will provide televisions,
soft furnishings, high chairs, and other equipment.
</TEXT>
