<HEADLINE>Long service awards</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>20</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974635185</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
LONG service and retirement certificates have been presented to 21 employees of
Dunecht Estates in Aberdeenshire. The presentations were made by the Hon
Charles Pearson who is joint owner of the estate with the trustees of the 3rd
Viscount Cowdray.
The late Lord Cowdray, who died in January of this year, owned the estates for
62 years and instigated the long service awards in 1977.
Two employees of the estate works department, foreman joiner D Christie and
foreman painter J Webster, received certificates marking their retirement after
49 years' service. Other retirement certificates were presented to R Leslie,
nurseryman (40 years);
G Bean, digger driver (39 years); W Fowler, tractorman (37 years); G Mackie,
draughtsman (33 years); W Scott, gardener, (28 years); J Auld, forester (22
years) and R McIntosh, estate accountant, (21 years).
Long Service awards for 40 years were presented to D Anderson, tractorman and J
Ewen, lorryman; 25 years - E Cruickshank, grieve; B Gilbert, tractorman; W
Davidson, shepherd; K Allan, tractorman; H Fergus, forester; I Fraser,
gamekeeper; A Gauld, painter;
J Macrae, navvy; R Calder, foreman navvy; and J Munro, joiner.
</TEXT>
